\begin_layout Standard
A temporary change means there is 
\series bold
no change in wealth
\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The supply curve doesn't change (because the change is 
\series bold

\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

tomorrow
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 
\series default
and not today).
 On the demand curve, the change will shift it to the right (firms want
 to take advantage of the higher productivity level).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We can immediately see that the interest rate increases (it won't hold because
 the change is temporary), and the total production increases as well.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Now that production has 2 uses - both consumption as investment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Consumption will be lower, as wealth did not change but the interest rate
 increased (people don't know anything about productivity levels - they
