\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The model tells nothing about the price level 
\begin_inset Formula $P$
\end_inset

, nor the nominal wage 
\begin_inset Formula $W^{n}$
\end_inset

.
 The reason is that money is simply not needed in that model, all equations
 can be solved in real terms, without involving anything nominal.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Households and firms need money in order to perform transactions (
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

medium of exchange
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 - gold, salt, cigarettes in WWII) which is necessary in almost any economy.
\end_layout

